  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "Building a Pyromancer in Dark Souls 3 can be a rewarding experience due to the class's versatility and powerful fire-based spells. Here\u2019s a guide on how to optimize your stats for an effective Pyromancer build:\n\n### Starting Class\nStart with the Pyromancer class, as it already has a balanced set of stats optimized for pyromancy.\n\n### Key Stats for Pyromancer\n\n1. **Intelligence (INT) and Faith (FTH)**:\n   - Both INT and FTH should be leveled equally as pyromancy scales with the lowest value between these two stats.\n   - Aim for a minimum of 30/30 INT/FTH to cast most pyromancies effectively.\n   - For late-game, consider going up to 40/40 INT/FTH for maximum damage output.\n\n2. **Attunement (ATT)**:\n   - Attunement increases your FP (Focus Points), which is essential for casting spells.\n   - Aim for at least 30 ATT to have enough FP and spell slots. You can go higher if you need more slots and FP.\n\n3. **Vigor (VIG)**:\n   - Vigor is crucial for survivability. Aim for at least 27 VIG, but ideally 40 for a good amount of HP.\n\n4. **Endurance (END)**:\n   - Endurance affects your stamina and equip load. Aim for at least 20 END, but you can go higher if you want more stamina or to wear heavier armor.\n\n5. **Vitality (VIT)**:\n   - Vitality increases your equipment load and a bit of your HP. It\u2019s less critical for a Pyromancer, but you may want to invest a few points to not be overburdened.\n\n6. **Strength (STR) and Dexterity (DEX)**:\n   - These are less important for a pure Pyromancer but can be useful if you want to use certain weapons that scale well with INT or FTH.\n   - The Pyromancer's starting weapon, the Flame Stone Hammer, requires 12 STR and 10 DEX, so you'll need at least this much.\n\n### Suggested Build Path:\n\n- **Early Game (Level 1-50)**:\n  - VIG: 27\n  - ATT: 24\n  - END: 20\n  - VIT: 10\n  - STR: 12\n  - DEX: 10\n  - INT: 30\n  - FTH: 30\n  - LCK: 7 (Base)\n\n- **Mid Game (Level 50-100)**:\n  - VIG: 35\n  - ATT: 30\n  - END: 25\n  - VIT: 15\n  - STR: 12\n  - DEX: 10\n  - INT: 40\n  - FTH: 40\n  - LCK: 7\n\n- **Late Game/End Game (Level 100+)**:\n  - VIG: 40\n  - ATT: 35\n  - END: 30\n  - VIT: 20\n  - STR: 12\n  - DEX: 10\n  - INT: 40\n  - FTH: 40\n  - LCK: 7\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Pyromancy Flame**: Upgrade your Pyromancy Flame regularly as it significantly increases your spell damage.\n- **Rings**: Consider using the Fire Clutch Ring to boost fire damage and the Sage Ring to reduce spell casting time.\n- **Spells**: Some key pyromancies to consider are Chaos Bed Vestiges, Great Chaos Fire Orb, and Black Flame. Also, consider using utility spells like Flash Sweat for added survivability.\n- **Weapons**: The Witch's Locks is a great weapon for Pyromancers as it scales well with INT and FTH and can be infused with fire.\n\nThis build should give you a strong foundation to succeed as a Pyromancer in Dark Souls 3. Happy gaming!",
